FeedPackage.Description:
Elegant audio player control in Windows Runtime Component
The Buddha is a component created to do a download and caching of audio files from a url. Buddha has a play, pause and download button, a progress ring to while the download of file is going on, an slider for manipulate the audio and the clock time. The Buddha is an excellent component to be used in chat apps.
To use, enough set a Url property value and choose a value of AutoLoad property, which if true the download start when the set Url value, if false, the download button appears and the user can tap to start download.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Play audios from a url and caching
